microHabitat: sandy beach with rock outcroppings, intertidal, Gracillaria washes with sand and holdfast
eventRemarks: beach almost entirely covered with Gracillaria and one other tufty red alga, very little Ulva, and lowest intertidal with eelgrass and assorted brown algae.  Mid-intertidal with a few very small stands very large Mytilus californianus (quite healthy looking 5-6- virtually no small individuals) interspersed with large colonies of Anthopleura elegantissima, very few barnacles and limpets including volcano limpets and occassional large chitons - only 4 specimens of A. elegantissima sampled and one volcano limpet.
